===[ Aqua DiveLog ]=======================================[ Aqua DiveLog ]===

- copy the contents of the install/adl/template/ dir to ADLs template/ dir
- copy the contents of the install/adl/ dir to ADLs directory
- adjust the DATADIR setting in the beginning of divelog_conduit.sh
- adjust the settings for TablePDBFile and DivePDBFile in both the divelog.data
  and divelog.sites files in the ADL directory

===[ phpDiveLog ]==========================================[ phpDiveLog ]===

2.1. Installation
-----------------
- copy everything except the install/ subdir into your web tree
- if you don't want to start with the demo data, remove all files from
  the data/ and fotos/ subdir

2.2. Configuration
------------------
All the "user-based" configuration takes place in the inc/config.inc file. I
strongly recommend not to try some configuration in other places - if you
miss some configuration option, just let me know and I will see if and how I
can implement this.

Each configuration option is documented within the config file, so I assume
there's no further explanation needed what the options stand for. Plus they
match all on one screen, so there are no hints required where to look for
what ;)

If in the divelog_conduit.sh file (see above in block 1) you adjusted the
DATADIR only (and did not change any file names), and the directory structure
in your ADL installation stayed the same as shipped, no more changes have to be
made. Run the conduit script once (otherwise you have my old dive data
displayed - if you didn't wipe them in step 2.1. above), and enjoy!

